User Feeling

Not:

“I’m selling my data”

But:

“I’m putting my signal to work”

⸻

2. CORE LOOP (THE ENGINE)

This is the heart:

Loop
	1.	User generates data (passively or actively)
	2.	Data flows into allocated pools
	3.	Pools are accessed by companies/models
	4.	Value is generated (training, insights, revenue)
	5.	Attribution engine distributes yield
	6.	User sees:
	•	earnings
	•	performance
	•	recommendations
	7.	User reallocates (optional)

→ repeat

⸻

3. THE THREE ENGINES (REAL MOAT)

A. Signal Engine (Data Processing Layer)

Transforms raw data into usable units:
	•	cleans data
	•	normalizes formats
	•	anonymizes
	•	tags with metadata:
	•	quality
	•	rarity
	•	freshness
	•	domain

Output:

Standardized “Signal Units”

⸻

B. Contribution Engine (Attribution Layer)

This is the hardest—and most important.

Calculates:

“How much did THIS user’s data contribute to value?”

Methods (stacked, not single):
	•	cohort comparison
	•	ablation testing (remove data → measure drop)
	•	similarity clustering
	•	edge-case detection (rare = higher value)
	•	temporal weighting (recent = more valuable)

Output:

Contribution Score per user per pool

⸻

C. Yield Engine (Payout Layer)

Distributes value:
	•	real-time micro accrual
	•	periodic payouts (daily/weekly)
	•	bonus multipliers for:
	•	exclusivity
	•	consistency
	•	high-impact signals

Output:

Data Dividends

⸻

4. NEW PRIMITIVE (THIS IS YOUR EDGE)

“Signal Units” (SU)

Instead of “data blobs,” everything becomes:

Atomic, priced units of signal

Each unit has:
	•	origin (user)
	•	category
	•	quality score
	•	uniqueness score
	•	timestamp
	•	usage permissions

This enables:
	•	pricing
	•	trading
	•	bundling
	•	attribution

⸻

