⸻

Key Upgrade

Funds now show:
	•	APY (Annual Percentage Yield for data)
	•	Volatility
	•	Demand Trend
	•	Signal Scarcity

⸻

6. MARKET DYNAMICS (WHERE IT GETS POWERFUL)

A. Supply vs Demand for Data
	•	Companies bid for data types
	•	Rare data → higher yield
	•	Oversupplied data → lower yield

Example:
	•	generic browsing = cheap
	•	verified medical outcomes = expensive

⸻

B. Data Auctions (Advanced Layer)

Companies can:
	•	request specific datasets
	•	set budgets
	•	define constraints

Users can:
	•	opt in
	•	earn premium rates

⸻

C. Exclusivity Premiums

If user grants:

“Only this company can use this data”

→ payout multiplier

⸻

7. DEFENSE LAYER (TRUST SYSTEM)

Privacy by Architecture
	•	raw data rarely leaves system
	•	companies interact via:
	•	queries
	•	models
	•	aggregated outputs

Trust Scores

For companies:
	•	payout reliability
	•	data usage compliance
	•	user satisfaction

For users:
	•	data authenticity
	•	consistency
	•	signal quality

⸻

8. FRAUD & GAME THEORY (HOUND LAYER)

People will try to game it.

You counter with:
	•	anomaly detection (pattern breaks)
	•	cross-validation across sources
	•	reputation decay for bad actors
	•	delayed payout for suspicious signals
	•	synthetic data detection

⸻

9. MVP (BUILD THIS FIRST)

Don’t overbuild.

Week 1–2
	•	Data wallet (basic connections)
	•	2–3 funds only
	•	simple allocation UI

Week 3–4
	•	basic payout simulation (even fake at first)
	•	dashboard:
	•	“you earned $X from your data”

Week 5–6
	•	real pilot with:
	•	1–2 companies
	•	1 niche dataset (fitness, shopping, etc.)

⸻

MVP Insight

You don’t need perfect attribution at first.

You need:

belief + feedback loop

